<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,2032]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. External characters similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 2014" authorityName="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2014" box="[617,1108,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[617,758,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. lamellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Camara" box="[765,1108,258,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" refString="Camara, J. T., Plant, A. R. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2014) Neotropical Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae), a world of discovery I: New generic record and new species from Brazilian Amazon basin. Zootaxa, 3893 (2), 209 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3893.2.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Câmara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 
<number box="[1048,1108,259,283]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Cercus wide basally, bluntly pointed at apex (
<figureCitation box="[348,434,293,318]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[404,434,294,318]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
), left and right cerci separated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[981,1069,293,318]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[1037,1069,294,318]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus with hook, and apical membranous area covered with spicules (
<figureCitation box="[611,695,329,354]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[663,695,330,354]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes very long (
<figureCitation box="[1253,1423,329,354]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Figs 31, 34, 
<number box="[1392,1423,329,354]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="206" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,2032]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,365,390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,417,365,390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,527,365,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,527,365,389]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,615,365,390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[480,494,401,425]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[847,889,436,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
frontal setulae; 
<number box="[1081,1095,436,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of distinct vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate row of smaller postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense, short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct, short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[888,922,542,567]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1253,1288,543,567]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,385,577,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[403,491,577,602]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[459,491,578,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; thoracic dorsum yellow except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, on scutum posterolaterally above wing base and laterally on scutellum and mediotergite; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight and scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except 
<number box="[397,411,685,709]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural and 
<number box="[600,614,685,709]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of scutellars, the inner stronger. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1044,1100,684,709]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1115,1199,684,709]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1199,685,709]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[1426,1436,685,709]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[173,206,720,744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.3">1.3</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[593,603,720,744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[706,740,720,743]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">7X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[1333,1343,720,744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1350,1383,720,744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[268,279,755,779]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number box="[295,329,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="4.5">4.5</number>
–5.0X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number box="[811,825,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[834,905,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18</number>
/ 
<number box="[914,923,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[940,1010,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18</number>
/ 
<number box="[1020,1064,755,780]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
; basal spines stronger; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[361,399,791,815]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="0.9">0.9</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number box="[886,900,791,815]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity. T 
<number box="[1401,1411,791,815]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[151,186,826,850]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[365,376,826,850]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; about 
<number box="[1018,1088,826,850]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20–23</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[1384,1394,862,886]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong apical spine. Mid- and hind legs slender with fine setae; T 
<number box="[938,950,897,921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,216,932,957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[232,317,932,957]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[285,317,933,957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane slightly yellow, veins yellowish; R 
<number box="[857,865,947,961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[874,881,947,961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[391,476,971,995]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[784,792,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[868,876,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[910,918,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[927,934,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="5.0">5</number>
fork acute (~ 
<number box="[1094,1126,970,995]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[1412,1417,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1427,1436,985,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about same length as R 
<number box="[498,506,1024,1038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[539,547,1024,1038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[625,633,1024,1038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally, diverging slightly at extreme apex; R 
<number box="[1279,1287,1024,1038]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<date box="[1315,1350,1009,1033]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
<number box="[1315,1328,1009,1033]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number box="[201,209,1062,1076]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[665,673,1062,1076]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<date box="[702,738,1047,1071]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
<number box="[702,716,1047,1071]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1210,1327,1047,1072]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Figs 28, 30</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number box="[304,346,1085,1110]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
and 
<number box="[405,419,1086,1110]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish; tergites 
<number box="[643,657,1086,1109]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellow with pale setae most conspicuous on posterior margin; tergite 
<number box="[325,339,1121,1145]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="8.0">8</number>
longer than sternite 
<number box="[573,589,1121,1145]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="8.0">8</number>
; membranous area between segment 
<number box="[1013,1027,1121,1145]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="8.0">8</number>
and terminalia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1212,1343,1121,1146]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Cercus brown, wide basally, bluntly pointed at apex (
<figureCitation box="[694,781,1156,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[751,781,1157,1181]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
), left and right cerci separated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1423,1156,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,1157,1181]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
), distinctly setose. Epandrium yellowish, narrow, rounded at apex, scattered strong setae on outer face (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1422,1191,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1422,1192,1216]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
); articulated to hypandrium by weak point anteriorly. Surstylus narrow, with spine-like setae on inner face (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Figs 32, 33</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium brownish, rather subrectangular (
<figureCitation box="[740,827,1262,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[796,827,1262,1287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
), with distinct setae; gonocoxal apodeme very long, projecting much beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[850,1099,1298,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Figs 30, 31, 34, 35</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite with subquadrate anterior projection and median subrounded posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1097,1333,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[1066,1097,1334,1358]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus strongly sclerotized basally, extending well beyond hypandrium apex, with hook and apical membranous area, covered with spicules (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1404,1429]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,244,1405,1429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme unilamellar plate flattened in vertical plane, ~ 
<number box="[1026,1061,1405,1429]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1440,1465]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,1440,1464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[263,459,1440,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Specimen length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[474,563,1440,1464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,713,1440,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[729,818,1440,1464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,915,1440,1465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
