<quantity box="[635,770,1689,1713]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5999999999999996" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.5999999999999996" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.9 mm</quantity>
and wing length varying from 
<quantity box="[1118,1256,1688,1713]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="206" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,258,2032]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1724,1749]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[321,663,1724,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,663,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Hemerodromia megalamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[670,760,1724,1749]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[670,760,1724,1749]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
appears to belong to the same group of species that includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 2014" authorityName="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2014" box="[151,642,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. lamellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Camara" box="[299,642,1759,1784]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" refString="Camara, J. T., Plant, A. R. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2014) Neotropical Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae), a world of discovery I: New generic record and new species from Brazilian Amazon basin. Zootaxa, 3893 (2), 209 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3893.2.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Câmara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 
<number box="[583,642,1760,1784]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 2014" authorityName="Camara, Plant &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2014" box="[654,1201,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata">
<emphasis box="[654,852,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Camara" box="[860,1201,1759,1784]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" refString="Camara, J. T., Plant, A. R. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2014) Neotropical Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae), a world of discovery I: New generic record and new species from Brazilian Amazon basin. Zootaxa, 3893 (2), 209 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3893.2.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Câmara, Plant &amp; Rafael, 
<number box="[1145,1201,1760,1784]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1256,1436,1759,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="membranosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1256,1436,1759,1783]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. membranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,241,1795,1820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,241,1795,1820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, characterized by a membranous area between segment 
<number box="[878,892,1795,1819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="8.0">8</number>
and male terminalia, with very long ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes. 
<taxonomicName box="[454,798,1830,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[454,798,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Hemerodromia megalamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[808,899,1830,1855]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[808,899,1830,1855]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1054,1196,1830,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis box="[1054,1196,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. lamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the cercus wide basally and abruptly pointed distally; epandrium inflated basally, narrower distally and phallus with membranous area covered with small spicules (
<figureCitation box="[697,784,1901,1926]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[752,784,1902,1926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[806,1151,1901,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[806,1151,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">Hemerodromia megalamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1161,1253,1901,1926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1253,1901,1926]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">H. lamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the cercus not curved up distally (
<figureCitation box="[764,846,1936,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,200,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Hemerodromia megalamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 28, habitus, lateral view; 29, wing; 30, abdomen from tergite 6 to terminalia, lateral view; 31, terminalia, lateral view; 32, terminalia, dorsal view; 33, subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, ventral view; 34, phallus, gonocoxal apodeme and hypandrium, lateral view; 35, hypandrium, gonocoxal and ejaculatory apodemes, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233677/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="206">
Fig. 
<number box="[817,846,1937,1961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="206" value="31.0">31</number>
